The paper focuses on visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper explores the balance between model expressiveness and simplicity, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates the predictive power of its models, which involves information retrieval and ranking, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
